'''Robert Gillespie''' (28 April 1901 – 11 August 1960), sometimes known as '''Bob Gillespie''',<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://vintagefootballers.com/product/gillespie-bob-image-1-queens-park-1925/|title=Gillespie Bob Image 1 Queen's Park 1925|website=Vintage Footballers|language=en-GB|access-date=25 December 2018}}</ref> was a Scottish amateur [[Association football|football]] [[centre half]] who made over 420 appearances in the [[Scottish League]] for [[Queen's Park F.C.|Queen's Park]].<ref name="QPFC">{{Cite web |url=http://www.qpfc.com/appearances/g/gillespier.htm |title=QPFC.com – A Historical Queen's Park FC Website |website=www.qpfc.com |access-date=15 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book |title=Scotland's Who's Who: One Hundred and Forty Years of Scottish International Footballers 1872–2013 |last=Smith |first=Paul |date=30 September 2013 |publisher=Pitch Publishing Ltd |isbn=9781909178847 |edition= First |location=Durrington |page=100 |language=English}}</ref><ref name="Litster">{{Cite book |title=Record of Pre-War Scottish League Players |last=Litster |first=John |publisher=PM Publications |location=Norwich}}</ref> He was capped by Scotland at [[Scotland national football team|full]] and [[Scotland national amateur football team|amateur]] level and represented the [[Scottish League XI]].<ref>{{SFA Profile|id=112954|name=Robert Gillespie}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.londonhearts.com/scotland/players/robertgillespie.html |title=Robert Gillespie |work=www.londonhearts.com |publisher=London Hearts Supporters' Club |date= |accessdate=26 April 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.londonhearts.com/SFL/players/rgillespie.html |title=R Gillespie|work=www.londonhearts.com |publisher=London Hearts Supporters' Club |date= |accessdate=26 April 2014}}</ref><ref name="McColl">{{Cite web |url=http://www.scottish-football-historical-archive.co.uk/Forgotten%20Glories.pdf |title=FORGOTTEN GLORIES – British Amateur Internationals 1901–1974 |last=McColl |first=Brian |last2=Gorman |first2=Douglas |page=326 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170702210501/http://www.scottish-football-historical-archive.co.uk/Forgotten%20Glories.pdf |archive-date=2 July 2017 |dead-url=yes |access-date=19 July 2017 |last3=Campbell |first3=George}}</ref>

